title: Pink Floyd The Wall Movie Original Laserdisc (audio) 24/96
description:
Pink Floyd's The Wall Movie original 1982 Laserdisc (much better sounding than the previous 1991 re-release)This also does not have the annoying problem on 'Comfortably Numb' like the Deluxe Letterbox edition has where one channels volume goes down. 

Equipment: Full Analog (the Laserdisc is Analog not Digital Audio)

Laserdisc player Onkyo DX-V801

Amp 1979 Harman Kardon 670 Receiver (recently serviced no hum) 

Recorded in Audacity 24/96 highest settings.
